1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,120
Honestly…

2
00:00:01,880 --> 00:00:02,800
Why do you even like me?

3
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:04,080
with such a lovable soul

4
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:05,840
Who wouldn’t fall in love?

5
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,320
They love you.

6
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:10,200
I’m sorry.

7
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:14,760
You work and take care of your family.

8
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:16,320
You’re all grown up, alright.

9
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,160
But did I take care of you properly?

10
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,720
Are you going back to being a mall owner?

11
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:22,240
But how will I see you after this?

12
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:25,000
You want to know Tim better?

13
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:28,240
Was it a good day or a bad day?

14
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:29,520
It’s been a good day.

15
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:47,720
Everything okay?

16
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:51,840
I dropped the hair dryer.

17
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,120
I see…

18
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:04,760
Why don’t you sit down?

19
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,960
I’ll dry your hair.

20
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:01,920
We’re done.

21
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:08,320
I’ll sleep on U’s couch.

22
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:11,400
Okay.

23
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:12,680
YOU KNOW WHO IS BAD

24
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:14,960
Hey, Tim?

25
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:23,240
Why didn’t you just stay at Pai’s?

26
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,360
I’d better not.

27
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,960
Too much chemistry.

28
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:28,280
Things could get out of hand.

29
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,440
Let’s get in.

30
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:36,000
But why does it matter
if something happens?

31
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,440
I can’t let that happen.

32
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,200
Our relationship is complicated enough as it is.

33
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,040
Complicated?

34
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,240
You love him.

35
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,720
He loves you.

36
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:50,800
It’s just that simple.

37
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:58,960
For Pai, love and second chances
are two different things.

38
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:05,360
So what, now you’re just
some guy chasing after him?

39
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,160
Pretty much.

40
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,560
Does that mean anyone
could shoot his shot with him?

41
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,360
Don’t jinx it!

42
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:21,160
I’m hopeless enough as it is
without any rivals.

43
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:25,240
What are you hoping for, though?

44
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,160
I want to marry him.

45
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:35,600
You do?

46
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,320
When I signed that marriage certificate,

47
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:47,120
I knew right away
we were meant to be partners,

48
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,680
in life and legally.

49
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:55,160
We’re meant to be family,
not just boyfriends.

50
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,040
But…

51
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:04,960
Can we really marry
the same person twice?

52
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,440
U.

53
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:16,680
U!

54
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,160
Yes?

55
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:19,840
Where’s your mind at?

56
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,280
What are you thinking?

57
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,280
And don’t lie.

58
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:31,480
Are you wracking your brain
for the new campaign?

59
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,880
Do you plan to please our manager?

60
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,520
Tell me your ideas.

61
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:44,400
I’m thinking about marriage.

62
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,440
Marriage…

63
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:56,440
A collaboration campaign with
the house decor department, huh?

64
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:02,000
What do you think about marriage?

65
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:05,880
I don’t think it’s going to work.

66
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,760
It’s too group-specific.

67
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,840
I don’t find that interesting myself.

68
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:11,800
Not at all?

69
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:17,240
For me, marriage has become unromantic.

70
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,520
It’s just a legal process.

71
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,920
If that’s the theme you’re thinking about,
count me out.

72
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:26,520
Right.

73
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,640
(You’re so over the top with this.)

74
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:56,880
(I’m only back as a head of department, not the CEO, you know.)

75
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,040
(That’s not mine.)

76
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:00,440
Oh?

77
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,640
Come in.

78
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,720
I knew you’d like it.

79
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:23,640
Don’t leave me on read, Pai.

80
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,640
Text me back!

81
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,600
Hey, U?

82
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:29,680
You at work?

83
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,760
Help me find out
who sent Pai a rose bouquet.

84
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,120
Red roses to welcome me back?

85
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,320
Why not?

86
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,080
They’re perfect for you.

87
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:39,920
That’s good enough for me.

88
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,120
U, North, I told you to

89
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,720
I promise I will knock next time.

90
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:53,240
Oh!

91
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,280
What a beautiful bouquet.

92
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,360
Did you give Pai that, Kuea?

93
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:58,720
Yes.

94
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:03,400
I don’t think people usually send red roses
for simple congratulations, you know?

95
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:06,480
This is weird.

96
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,920
It’s okay as long as you like it.

97
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:26,680
The flowers are so beautiful
I have to snap a shot for future reference.

98
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:29,760
That’s nice, actually.

99
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,040
Send me the photos, too.

100
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:35,800
Oh, sure thing.

101
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:41,960
Kuea, you jerk!

102
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,400
Where’s your hand?

103
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,560
Don’t tell me it’s on Pai’s waist!

104
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:50,080
What?

105
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:51,640
How did you get in here?

106
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:52,760
What are you doing here?

107
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,280
Traffic was bad.
I needed to pee.

108
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:56,680
Prem.

109
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:58,480
My house isn’t a damn gas station.

110
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,440
I’m already having a bad day, man.

111
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:02,800
What got you so worked up?

112
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:04,640
Look.

113
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:07,880
He has a new boyfriend?

114
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,880
No, he doesn’t!

115
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,040
But I’m sure Kuea is making his move.

116
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,720
I know he’s been eyeing Pai for a while.

117
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,160
If I was eyeing him, I’d have made
my move now as well.

118
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:21,960
Making a move right after a breakup
has an 80% success rate.

119
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,600
What good does that information do me?

120
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,600
It doesn’t help that I’m waiting for him.

121
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:31,240
What are you waiting for, though?

122
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,880
You did all that to him,

123
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,160
and expect him to make the first move?

124
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,280
I’m waiting for him to be ready.

125
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,040
Listen to me, you dummy.

126
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,360
He’s been in pain.

127
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:47,280
He has trust issues now.

128
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:51,640
The only person still has faith
in this relationship is you.

129
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:57,040
So you’re the one who has
to find a way to start over, not Pai.

130
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,760
What took you so long to tell me this?

131
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:09,640
Let me ask you something.

132
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,760
Would it be rude if I go to him now?

133
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:18,160
You have the audacity
to go back to Empire?

134
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:19,520
For real?

135
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:21,360
Ugh!

136
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:22,880
This is annoying!

137
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:33,400
It’d be nice to have my real estate
booth at your event.

138
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:34,840
I’ll find a spot for you.

139
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,360
Please come in.

140
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:40,240
U.

141
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,040
What’s the matter?

142
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:52,560
U and I just want to learn more about leasing.

143
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:53,680
Right.

144
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:54,760
Am I right, U?

145
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:55,160
Exactly.
That’s a good idea.

146
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,200
Go on.
I’ll continue.

147
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:14,960
If we’re successful with the booth,
I’m thinking I could have a shop here.

148
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:16,800
Hold on…

149
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,480
Selling houses in a mall?

150
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,320
Why not?

151
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:21,000
We even sell Rolls-Royce here.

152
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:25,760
But no one wants to buy a house anymore.

153
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,560
They probably prefer condominiums.

154
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:33,520
You know what I do when
I get asked this question?

155
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,200
Please.

156
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,360
Don’t do that again.

157
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,000
Let’s play a game with this tennis ball.

158
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:47,920
There’s only one rule: Don’t drop the ball.

159
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:50,520
What does that have to do with houses?

160
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:55,200
Let’s begin.

161
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,320
North.

162
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:01,200
Ugh.

163
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:11,800
See?

164
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:16,120
Throwing a tennis ball in a
limited space is frustrating.

165
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:20,000
But if there’s more space,
that changes everything.

166
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:24,320
North.

167
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:26,480
Kuea, catch!

168
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:37,080
You see how sometimes there’s
more joy in the space you’re in?

169
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:41,440
When it comes to space,
houses still beat condominiums.

170
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,120
Alright.

171
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:43,680
Okay.

172
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:44,800
I’ll take one.

173
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:46,840
I just sold one house.

174
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,280
Let’s call it a day.

175
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:53,480
But I must request that
Pai catch this last one.

176
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:54,440
No.
I don’t want to play.

177
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,080
Catch, Pai!

178
00:14:58,880 --> 00:14:59,200
Pai!
Mr. Pai.

179
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:00,840
Mr. Pai.

180
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,240
Where does it hurt?

181
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,400
I think I might have sprained my ankle.

182
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:05,880
Let me see.

183
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:09,160
Kuea, you don’t have to.

184
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:10,840
I’ll take care of him.

185
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:17,840
Let me down already.

186
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,280
I can walk to the sofa on my own.

187
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:20,480
No way.

188
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,440
I can’t risk you getting
any more injured, you know?

189
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,840
(Tim, Pai sprained his ankle.)

190
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:39,880
(Sorry. We were gonna have U carry him.)

191
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,520
(But I’d get so jealous…)

192
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,280
I can’t stand this anymore!

193
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:56,960
Excuse me, sir.

194
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,600
Visitors must exchange their badge.

195
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:01,720
I forgot my ID card.

196
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,120
Would a copy suffice?

197
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,360
It would not.
I must apologize.

198
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:07,800
But I’m…

199
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,080
Yes?

200
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,920
No. It’s…

201
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,080
Pai and I are

202
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:19,400
It’s alright.

203
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,200
He’s my guest.

204
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,920
I’m sorry, sir.

205
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:31,040
I’m new here.

206
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:31,920
I didn’t know.
It’s alright.

207
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,480
Thank you for letting me in.

208
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:56,840
And…

209
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:58,920
I’m sorry for everything.

210
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:09,200
I don’t accept baseless apologies
in random elevators.

211
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:18,520
Did you and Pai talk it out
about your relationship?

212
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:22,280
I want to ask Pai for a second chance.

213
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:26,680
I want to prove myself so he trusts me again.

214
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:31,600
You can prove your love to Pai.

215
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:36,080
But what will you do to regain my trust?

216
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,920
What matters most in your life?

217
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:48,360
My family.

218
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:52,600
Well, then, get us introduced.

219
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:59,600
And they’d better be your real family this time.

220
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,360
This is awful.

221
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:18,560
You need a new strategy
that doesn’t involve a tennis ball.

222
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,640
Come in.

223
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:25,720
Tim?

224
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,000
What are you doing here?

225
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:30,640
U texted me that you sprained your ankle.

226
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:31,520
I was worried.

227
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,040
Are you alright?

228
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:34,680
Don’t worry.

229
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,360
I already applied some ointment for him.

230
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,160
Are you alright?

231
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,720
Should we go to the doctor?

232
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:42,440
Let’s go.
Don’t be dramatic.

233
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,320
It was just a slip.

234
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:50,160
Pai.

235
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:52,920
It’s almost time for our dinner.

236
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,000
Where are you going?

237
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:58,400
We’ll be discussing work over dinner.

238
00:18:58,840 --> 00:18:59,920
U and North will be there too.

239
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:02,400
Let me come, too.
I don’t think you should.

240
00:19:04,320 --> 00:19:05,600
It’s for work, after all.

241
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:09,720
Bye.

242
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,160
Can you walk?

243
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:18,720
Let me support you.

244
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:19,560
Let go.

245
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:20,920
Pai, let me do it.

246
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,640
Shouldn’t I be taking care of you?

247
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:29,000
I can take care of him just fine.

248
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:30,520
Stay out of this.

249
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:31,960
You stay out of this.

250
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,520
Pai and I are working together today.

251
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,400
It’s you who’s intervening, Tim.

252
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:36,920
Enough!

253
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:38,640
Both of you can back off.

254
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,000
I can take care of myself.

255
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:53,960
Oh, excuse me.

256
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:55,280
Excuse me.

257
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,560
Mr. Pai, wait for me!

258
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:00,000
Pai, wait for me, too!

259
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:00,480
North.

260
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,000
Hey, hey.
Where do you think you’re going?

261
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:12,480
What?

262
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,400
You follow Pai right now.

263
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,280
Don’t let Kuea get anywhere near him.

264
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,040
More importantly, do not let Pai get drunk.

265
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:21,680
If he does, you carry him home.

266
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:22,560
Got it?

267
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:25,840
If you’re gonna be this fussy,
why not just wait outside his door?

268
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:30,120
Good idea.

269
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:31,120
Give it to me.

270
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:32,200
What?

271
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,840
Your keycard.

272
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:34,640
Are you for real?
Yeah!

273
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,080
Here.

274
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,200
Now go.

275
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,360
Good job, brother-in-law.

276
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:40,000
Go!

277
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:41,200
Run!

278
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,240
Of course!

279
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:49,240
When will your legal team send us
feedback on the contract again?

280
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:52,120
You shouldn’t be talking about that.

281
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:53,520
We’re off work now.

282
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,960
You said we were going to discuss work.

283
00:20:59,040 --> 00:20:59,720
Alright.

284
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:03,240
I’ll get you the feedback by next week.

285
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:05,120
That’s it.

286
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,240
That’s all the work talk.

287
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:11,680
If you had a friend like that,
I’d be dying of jealousy.

288
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,000
Some friend, he is.

289
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,280
I can’t believe Pai can’t see it.

290
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:26,360
So… are you two still dating?

291
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,200
Yes.

292
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,680
Do you have a question, Kuea?

293
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,040
Just say it.

294
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,560
Your face is already saying half of it.

295
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:52,800
Well, then, I’ll be honest,
and I mean no offense.

296
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:59,200
How come you can still trust someone
who has lied to you?

297
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,600
If you don’t want to answer me, it’s alright.

298
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:17,280
It’s okay.

299
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:23,240
U has proven himself to me
that he really has changed.

300
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:27,880
Was it easy to forgive him?

301
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:29,000
Of course not.

302
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:30,840
Yes, he was wrong.

303
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:35,640
But he tried to fix his mistakes.

304
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:39,440
And I chose to forgive him.

305
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:45,840
If I want to be with him, there is
just no other way, is there?

306
00:22:58,160 --> 00:22:58,680
Thank you.

307
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,360
If it were me and my boyfriend said that,

308
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:03,800
I’d have asked him
to marry me on the spot.

309
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:07,560
Right.

310
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:26,960
What time do you think it is?

311
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:28,560
Why are you home so late?

312
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:29,840
What are you doing here?

313
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:32,040
You told me to wait here.

314
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,320
How come North is so drunk?

315
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:36,480
Hold on.

316
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:39,960
He’s not drunk.

317
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:42,120
He ate too much so he’s in a food coma.

318
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:45,360
But Pai…

319
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:46,800
He’s dead drunk.

320
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:48,640
Kuea had to take him home.

321
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:51,040
I wonder what’s going on with them now…

322
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:52,320
You dumbass!

323
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,640
Why did you let him do that?

324
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:55,480
I had to take care of North!

325
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:57,400
You idiot!

326
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,520
You’re unreliable as hell, you know that?

327
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:26,880
I like you, Pai.

328
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:31,280
Will you give me a chance?

329
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:36,920
What?

330
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:41,640
You look like you never had a clue before.

331
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:45,440
I never did.

332
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:51,360
I’ve been in love with you
for more than 10 years, Pai.

333
00:24:59,000 --> 00:24:59,480
Pai!

334
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:01,480
Pai.

335
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,040
Pai.

336
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:11,600
You’re drunk.

337
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:13,920
Don’t make any decisions now.

338
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:16,800
I’m not that drunk.

339
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:21,920
You.

340
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,520
What kind of man are you

341
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:27,280
to confess your love and ask for a chance
when he’s in this state?

342
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:30,080
And what kind of man are you

343
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:32,480
to come banging at your ex’s door
in the middle of the night?

344
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,400
Don’t you think you’re making
Pai uncomfortable?

345
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:37,400
Pai would never be uncomfortable
because of me.

346
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:38,600
Tim.

347
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:43,440
You’re acting like a loser who
can’t accept the truth right now.

348
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:44,240
Kuea.

349
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:45,560
That’s enough.

350
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:47,200
I’ll talk to him.

351
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:52,920
Are you gonna be alright?

352
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:54,680
I’m okay.

353
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,160
You should go home.

354
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:08,840
Come on in.

355
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,040
Why are you doing this?

356
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:30,840
I’m sorry I crossed a line.

357
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:32,720
I don’t need your sarcasm right now.

358
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:36,880
I’m not being sarcastic.

359
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:39,240
I really did cross a line.

360
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,560
Kuea had a point.

361
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,160
I’m your ex.

362
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,480
I shouldn’t be here.

363
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,120
I don’t see you the way Kuea does.

364
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:02,080
Then how do you see me?

365
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,600
I never stopped loving you.

366
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:14,320
But each time I try to trust you again,

367
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:17,800
I get so scared.

368
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:29,000
About that…

369
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:32,760
I believe I might need to spend
my whole life to prove it to you.

370
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,240
But in the mean time,

371
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:48,600
can we get back together?

372
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,280
Tim, I think

373
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:52,640
I talked to your Grandpa today.

374
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:59,040
He told me to introduce my family to yours.

375
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:00,160
What?

376
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,360
Once you know all parts of me,

377
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,600
and you still want me,

378
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:08,520
we’ll get back together.

379
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:17,560
But if in the end you want to move on
to someone else,

380
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:20,040
or want to remain friends,

381
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,560
I won’t cross your boundaries again.

382
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:30,680
And I promise to be a good friend to you.

383
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:32,480
I won't make you worry.

384
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,200
Alright?

385
00:28:55,560 --> 00:28:56,000
Hey.

386
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:57,200
What?

387
00:29:00,360 --> 00:29:03,200
I want to propose to North.

388
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:09,680
Congrats.

389
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:11,440
I hope you get what you want.

390
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:20,560
Hello.

391
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:22,200
What are you looking for today?

392
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,960
I’m looking for wedding rings.

393
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:25,960
Of course.

394
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:33,880
That one’s perfect for North.

395
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,000
Can I take a look at this one?

396
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:36,880
Of course.

397
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:38,440
Excuse me.

398
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:39,560
Can I take a look at this one, too?

399
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:40,560
Of course.

400
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,680
I’ll show you both sets.

401
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:44,440
Please take your time.

402
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:49,480
You can try it on your boyfriend.

403
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:52,280
He’s not my boyfriend.

404
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:54,360
I’m the groomsman.

405
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:56,760
My apologies.

406
00:29:57,720 --> 00:30:00,040
So your boyfriend isn’t here.

407
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:03,120
Do you know his ring size?

408
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:04,640
Oh…

409
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:05,800
Yes.

410
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:08,400
It’s…

411
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:15,200
This.

412
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,240
This is the size.

413
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:17,920
Please make it this big.

414
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:19,640
Of course. Please hang on.

415
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,040
Of course.

416
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:22,760
What about you, sir?

417
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,320
(If you still want me,)

418
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:43,360
(we’ll get back together.)

419
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:47,200
(But if in the end you want to move on to someone else,)

420
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:48,960
(I won’t cross your boundaries again.)

421
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:53,880
Come in.

422
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:02,120
Mr. Pai.

423
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:04,280
I need to talk to you.

424
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:07,800
Me?

425
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:09,560
Yes.

426
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:22,560
I…

427
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:27,200
I want to marry North.

428
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,680
If you still don’t trust me,

429
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:38,160
I’m more than happy to draft a contract
regarding North’s assets.

430
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:45,600
But North and I are more than
just boyfriends now.

431
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:52,560
What suddenly makes you
want to marry him again?

432
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:59,680
I was talking about marriages with Tim.

433
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:04,800
He said, to him, it’s starting his own family.

434
00:32:08,880 --> 00:32:16,160
It’s being each other’s partner
in life and legally

435
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:19,920
And I couldn’t agree more.

436
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:36,480
I think North is mature enough
to make his own decision.

437
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:41,080
If North says yes,
I’ll talk to Grandpa for you.

438
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,200
You will?

439
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:47,840
From now on you can call me by my name.

440
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:54,960
Of course, Pai.

441
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,400
Thank you.

442
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,080
It’s okay.

443
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:03,240
Thank you so much, Pai.

444
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:07,240
I’m so happy.

445
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:09,760
Pai. Pai.

446
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:17,840
Here’s the plan, Pai.

447
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:29,360
North.

448
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:31,440
I’ve been looking for you.

449
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:33,160
I want to give you a house tour.

450
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,600
Maybe you can help me with the PR.

451
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:35,800
I see.

452
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:37,160
Sure.

453
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:40,360
I’ll call U.

454
00:33:41,120 --> 00:33:41,680
No need.

455
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,080
We can go just the two of us.

456
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:46,320
I talked to your boss.

457
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:47,640
Let’s go.

458
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,160
Right.

459
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,760
Come on. Let’s get to work.

460
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:52,520
Hurry up.
Okay.

461
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:02,960
Here.
Let me help.

462
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,480
How tasteless.

463
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:11,520
It’s perfect for U and North, though.

464
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:13,440
What do you mean?

465
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:17,480
It’s basic but genuine.

466
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:27,560
KUEA
(North and I are almost there.)

467
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:29,440
Kuea is almost here with North.

468
00:34:29,640 --> 00:34:30,320
You ready?

469
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:32,040
U!

470
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:33,600
North is almost here.

471
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:34,560
You done?
I’m almost done!

472
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:35,640
Hey.

473
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:37,520
Hurry up.

474
00:34:48,680 --> 00:34:49,320
What?

475
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:52,240
You… You know of this house?

476
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:56,040
Don’t tell me you’re a scammer, too!

477
00:34:58,120 --> 00:34:58,680
North.

478
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:00,680
Take a deep breath.

479
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:03,640
Now go inside.

480
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:08,880
Go on.

481
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:47,000
U.

482
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:54,600
North.

483
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:57,120
Will you give me another chance?

484
00:35:58,560 --> 00:36:01,520
I promise to take good care of you.

485
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:08,000
We’ll… make it our real home.

486
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:34,080
Will you marry me?

487
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:37,440
Yes.

488
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:39,200
I will.

489
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:23,520
You said yes too quickly.

490
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:25,400
I spent hours making this
and you totally wasted it.

491
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:27,680
I love him, duh.

492
00:37:34,040 --> 00:37:35,400
Guys, let’s take a photo.

493
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:36,040
Okay.
Alright.

494
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:40,720
Kuea, can you take a photo for us?

495
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:41,760
Wow.

496
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:44,600
Is this why I’m here?

497
00:37:45,040 --> 00:37:45,800
Of course not.

498
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:47,880
Let’s take a photo.

499
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,080
Do your best, Kuea.

500
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:52,280
Alright. Let’s take that photo.

501
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:52,880
Let’s pose for a photo.

502
00:37:58,600 --> 00:37:59,800
One, two, three.

503
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:01,760
Let’s take one video as well.

504
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:04,120
Let’s say “He said yes” together.

505
00:38:04,640 --> 00:38:06,680
One, two, three.

506
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:09,560
He said yes!
I said yes!

507
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:12,800
I have a polaroid here.

508
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:13,680
Let’s take one.

509
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:14,960
Alright.
Okay.

510
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:16,680
Kuea, get in the photo.

511
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:19,680
Come on in right next to me.

512
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:23,160
Kuea, you’re out of the frame.

513
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:25,760
Sorry but can you crouch down?

514
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:26,920
Lower.

515
00:38:27,720 --> 00:38:29,360
Let’s say “He said yes” again together.

516
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:30,760
One, two, three.

517
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:32,800
He said yes!
He said yes!

518
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,280
North, put that here.

519
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:43,920
Pure bailed out on us, huh?

520
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:45,200
And he was the one who brought all these.

521
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:48,360
Let me help.

522
00:38:49,120 --> 00:38:49,840
No, you don’t.

523
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:51,680
Go back and celebrate with North.

524
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:54,000
And don’t forget to call Grandpa.

525
00:38:54,760 --> 00:38:58,000
We’ll go to him to ask for his blessing officially soon.

526
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:00,720
Alright.

527
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:04,680
Thank you for giving me the loan
for the house again, Pai.

528
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:06,760
Hmm!

529
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:09,000
You call him by his name now?

530
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:15,320
He said a whole sentence,
and that’s the part you comprehend?

531
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:20,360
Thank you for today, Pai.

532
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:24,880
Bye.

533
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:25,920
Bye, Tim.
Goodbye.

534
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:27,320
Bye.
See you, Tim.

535
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:28,400
See ya.

536
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:31,920
Shall we go?

537
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,000
I’ll give you a ride.

538
00:39:38,240 --> 00:39:38,920
No.

539
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:40,600
I need to talk to Kuea.

540
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:46,640
Kuea.

541
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:55,960
Hmm?

542
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:58,120
Wait outside.

543
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:11,520
I told you I like you.

544
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:14,480
I asked for a chance.

545
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:17,960
Do you have an answer for me now?

546
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:42,000
Where are you going?

547
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,640
You said you were going to
give me a ride home.

548
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:48,280
I thought you’d go home with Kuea.

549
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,080
You were holding his hands.

550
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:51,800
Why are you upset?

551
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:02,080
You said you’d still be a good friend to me
even if I chose someone else.

552
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:04,200
Fine!
Sure!

553
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:06,720
I’d be the perfect friend.

554
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,240
Let me just calm down a bit.

555
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:13,360
I turned him down.

556
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:15,720
He’s a friend.

557
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:19,080
I told him not to wait for me.

558
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:20,960
Because he and I can never
be anything else.

559
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:27,880
Does that mean there’s a chance for me?

560
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:38,000
You said you wanted an answer from me
after we meet your parents.

561
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:39,880
I’m alright with that.

562
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:41,800
I’ll give you an answer after that.

563
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:44,680
Of course.

564
00:41:45,680 --> 00:41:46,240
Let’s go.

565
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:47,400
I’ll give you a ride.

566
00:41:50,520 --> 00:41:51,280
Don’t touch me.

567
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:52,680
Sorry.

568
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:02,520
Hey.

569
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:05,440
U.

570
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,400
We still need it for the wedding.

571
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:19,840
I can’t wait to put a ring on your finger.

572
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:26,960
Thank you for asking me to marry you.

573
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:31,640
Thank you for saying yes.

574
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:41,480
What was Tim like as a child?

575
00:42:43,040 --> 00:42:44,960
It was a tough time for our family when Tim was young.

576
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:51,440
He always acted like a hero, doing anything he could to help us out.

577
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:55,680
We had to tell him we were used to struggling

578
00:42:56,680 --> 00:42:58,080
and that we needed him to only take good care of himself.

579
00:42:59,120 --> 00:42:59,920
Look at him now.

580
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:01,840
He’s taking care of his boyfriend.

581
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:07,760
Did you know he’s a con artist who scams people to pay his debts?

582
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:09,600
Sir…

583
00:43:11,280 --> 00:43:11,880
That…

584
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,800
He conned my grandson.

585
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:15,880
Grandpa.

586
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:18,040
What is this about, Tim?

587
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:28,760
I’m sorry.

588
00:43:32,920 --> 00:43:34,280
It’s just as he said.

589
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:35,440
Tim.

590
00:43:44,680 --> 00:43:45,400
Excuse me.

591
00:44:02,280 --> 00:44:02,560
Papa.
Mama.

592
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:07,400
I just wanted our family to be back to how we were.

593
00:44:09,720 --> 00:44:11,800
We used to be so happy.

594
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:17,160
But now…

595
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:21,960
You’re getting old

596
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:25,160
and still working for someone else,

597
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:28,800
laboring away your bodies,

598
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:31,400
and sleeping in a tiny flat.

599
00:44:33,800 --> 00:44:34,640
I just can’t accept it.

600
00:44:37,440 --> 00:44:37,680
Tim.

601
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:42,280
Do you think your mother and I would be happy

602
00:44:44,400 --> 00:44:47,600
if the money you give us is dirty?

603
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:51,560
We would rather struggle

604
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,120
than have you do something like this.

605
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:07,640
I’m sorry.

606
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:12,320
I’ll quit.

607
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:19,920
Will you forgive me?

608
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:24,520
Tim.

609
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:31,360
You don’t have to do anything for us from now on.

610
00:45:33,960 --> 00:45:37,120
Your mother and I really are okay.

611
00:45:38,960 --> 00:45:39,400
Yes.

612
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:42,440
I’m so sorry.

613
00:46:02,720 --> 00:46:04,440
I really must ask for your forgiveness, Mr. Soepohn.

614
00:46:06,240 --> 00:46:08,640
We really don’t know how we’d make it up to you.

615
00:46:10,120 --> 00:46:12,240
But we really are sorry.

616
00:46:15,560 --> 00:46:16,480
Papa. Mama.

617
00:46:16,880 --> 00:46:18,520
Please, get up.

618
00:46:19,760 --> 00:46:21,120
Let’s not go to such extremes.

619
00:46:30,040 --> 00:46:35,840
All this time, Tim has been proving to us that he’s really sorry for what he did

620
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:39,160
and that he loves my grandson.

621
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:49,240
But in all honesty, for me, he still has so much to prove.

622
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:52,600
But I won’t get in his way

623
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:58,560
if Pai wants to give him a chance.

624
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:05,560
Really, sir?

625
00:47:12,080 --> 00:47:13,920
I’m willing to spend my whole life proving myself to you.

626
00:47:22,200 --> 00:47:23,720
I’m sorry for what happened, Pai.

627
00:47:24,760 --> 00:47:27,160
And I must thank you that you’re willing to give my son a chance.

628
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,320
Yes, ma’am.

629
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:42,960
You can’t control them, you can only raise them, indeed.

630
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:09,080
Just sell the house and pay him back with that money.

631
00:48:09,640 --> 00:48:09,840
Yes.

632
00:48:10,640 --> 00:48:12,080
Have a safe trip, you guys.

633
00:48:14,960 --> 00:48:15,200
Let’s go.

634
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:35,240
You sent your Grandpa off?

635
00:48:39,840 --> 00:48:42,160
Can I talk to you?

636
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:45,160
Of course.

637
00:48:53,960 --> 00:48:56,520
So that was what my life was like before this.

638
00:48:58,600 --> 00:49:02,080
I know it’s no excuse for me to hurt people.

639
00:49:08,040 --> 00:49:09,000
I won’t lie to you again.

640
00:49:12,520 --> 00:49:14,080
I don’t believe everything you said, Tim.

641
00:49:19,160 --> 00:49:19,440
But…

642
00:49:22,560 --> 00:49:24,320
I’ll give you another chance.

643
00:49:30,440 --> 00:49:31,480
Let’s get back together.

644
00:49:36,520 --> 00:49:37,000
You mean it?

645
00:49:39,080 --> 00:49:39,920
Don’t change your mind.

646
00:49:40,480 --> 00:49:40,880
Of course.

647
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:44,280
But we’ll take it slow.

648
00:49:48,560 --> 00:49:48,960
Of course.

649
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:54,280
Can I at least call you “baby” again?

650
00:49:57,000 --> 00:49:57,800
Do what you want.

651
00:50:02,640 --> 00:50:02,840
Baby.

652
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:37,480
I give you my blessing and hope your marriage is full of happiness.

653
00:50:37,720 --> 00:50:39,280
Why do I want to get married?

654
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:41,560
I want to have a house

655
00:50:41,640 --> 00:50:42,800
where I can take care of you in sickness and in health.

656
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:45,680
But more than anything, I just want us to completely belong to each other.

657
00:50:52,960 --> 00:50:53,640
Will you marry me?

